# GitHub.com SSH host keys, pinned for the stamp-server image.
#
# Source: https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure/githubs-ssh-key-fingerprints
# Last verified: 2026-05-11 (re-verify before merging if the GitHub doc has
# changed; rotation events are announced via GitHub's blog and changelog).
#
# Why three key types: SSH clients negotiate which host-key algorithm to
# use during the handshake; pinning only ed25519 would force older clients
# (or constrained alpine setups) to fall back to TOFU on the other algos.
# Pinning all three lets git's bundled ssh pick whichever it prefers and
# still verify against this file.
#
# Rotation: when GitHub announces a host-key change, update this file and
# rebuild the image. The deploy itself is the cutover — running containers
# keep the old keys until redeployed. There is no in-band update path.
